Buffer {
    area: Rect { x: 0, y: 0, width: 80, height: 40 },
    content: [
        "Welcome to tracexec! The TUI consists of at most two panes: the event list and  ",
        "optionally the pseudo terminal if --tty/-t is enabled. The event list displays  ",
        "the events emitted by the tracer. The active pane's border is highlighted in    ",
        "cyan. To switch active pane, press  Ctrl+S . To send  Ctrl+S  to the pseudo     ",
        "terminal, press  Alt+S  when event list is active. The keybinding list at the   ",
        "bottom of the screen shows the available keys for currently active pane or      ",
        "popup.                                                                          ",
        "You can navigate the event list using the arrow keys or  H/J/K/L . To scroll    ",
        "faster, use  Ctrl+↑/↓/←/→/H/J/K/L  or  PgUp/PgDn . Use  (Shift +) Home/End  to  ",
        "scroll to the (line start/line end)/top/bottom. Press  F  to toggle follow mode,",
        "which will keep the list scrolled to bottom. To change pane size, press  G/S    ",
        "when the active pane is event list. To switch between horizontal and vertical   ",
        "layout, press  Alt+L . To view the details of the selected event, press  V . To ",
        "copy the selected event to the clipboard, press  C  then select what to copy. To",
        "jump to the parent exec event of the currently selected event, press  U . To    ",
        "show the backtrace of the currently selected event, press  T . To quit, press   ",
        " Q  while the event list is active.                                             ",
        "When the pseudo terminal is active, you can interact with the terminal using the",
        "keyboard.                                                                       ",
        "Each exec event in the event list consists of four parts, the pid, the status of",
        "the process,the comm of the process (before exec), and the commandline to       ",
        "reproduce the exec event. The pid is colored according to the result of the     ",
        "execve{,at} syscall.    The status can be one of the following:  ⚠️  Exec failed", // hidden by multi-width symbols: [(66, " ")]
        "(ENOENT) ,  ❌  Exec failed ,  🟢  Running ,  ⏸️  Paused ,  🛸  Detached ,      ", // hidden by multi-width symbols: [(13, " "), (32, " "), (47, " "), (61, " ")]
        " 😇  Exited normally ,  😡  Exited abnormally ,  🤬  Terminated ,  😵  Killed , ", // hidden by multi-width symbols: [(2, " "), (25, " "), (50, " "), (68, " ")]
        " 💥  Segfault ,  🥺  Interrupted ,  👿  Illegal instruction ,  😱  Aborted ,    ", // hidden by multi-width symbols: [(2, " "), (18, " "), (37, " "), (64, " ")]
        " 💀  Signaled ,  ⛔  An internal error occurred                                 ", // hidden by multi-width symbols: [(2, " "), (18, " ")]
        "                    Press  Any Key  to close this help popup.                   ",
        "                                                                                ",
        "                                                                                ",
